<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: EX-PARKS WORKER GETS 3 YEARS FOR MOLESTATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A former city employee at Reseda Park was sentenced to three years imprisonment 
Friday for molesting a 6-year-old boy. 
</P>
<P>
Lars Juden, 38, who coached young people in athletics at the park since 1983, 
pleaded guilty Friday to child molestation. 
</P>
<P>
In exchange for the plea, prosecutors dropped a second child molestation 
charge. 
</P>
<P>
Juden and another man, Ronald Ray Rudd, a 39-year-old volunteer at the park, 
molested the boy last July and August in the park office and in a van across 
the street. They were arrested in August, and Juden was fired. 
</P>
<P>
Van Nuys Superior Court Judge Kathryne Ann Stoltz could have sentenced Juden to 
up to eight years in prison, said Deputy Dist. Atty. Eduards R. Abele. But 
Abele said he was "quite satisfied" with Juden's sentence because the guilty 
plea saved the boy the pain of having to take the stand. Juden has no prior 
convictions for child molestation, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Rudd, who admitted that he has twice before been convicted of child 
molestation, was sentenced in September to 15 years in prison after he pleaded 
guilty to three counts of child molestation. 
</P>
<P>
At Juden's preliminary hearing, Los Angeles police Detective Joseph Diglio 
quoted Juden as saying, "If the kid didn't come to the park alone, these things 
wouldn't happen." 
</P>
</TEXT>
