<P>
HOORAY FOR THOSE WHO AMBUSH DUCKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thank you for the front-page article, "South for the Winter," on Jan. 16. 
</P>
<P>
Although I must admit that I have never experienced the thrilling sport of 
ambushing ducks from behind the bushes, I look up to macho-men like Mr. 
Missildine with sheer awe. 
</P>
<P>
After all, it takes a special kind of person to blast more than 2,000 birds in 
two days, just as it takes a special kind of newspaper to feature these types 
of American heroes. 
</P>
<P>
Maybe next week you can do an article on blinding deer with high-powered 
lights, then blasting them with semiautomatic rifles. How about chasing 
raccoons up trees with a pack of dogs and shooting them out of the branches? 
Whatever article it is, I can only hope it measures up to the standards 
established by your detailed profile of those who blow ducks out of the sky. 
</P>
<P>
By the way, cancel my subscription. 
</P>
<P>
MICHAEL VOGT, Valencia 
