<HEADLINE>
<P>
CSUN VOLLEYBALL TEAM RALLIES TO POST VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The slow-starting Cal State Northridge volleyball team needed another rally to 
post its second consecutive win, defeating San Diego State, 6-15, 15-17, 15-7, 
15-13, 15-11, in a nonconference match. 
</P>
<P>
Neil Coffman led the visiting Matadors (2-1) with 30 kills, and Raphael Tulino 
and Coley Kyman each had 20 kills. Doug Potter led the Aztecs (0-1) with 19 
kills. 
</P>
