<HEADLINE>
<P>
'DRUG WARS': MEXICO, U.S. GOVERNMENT AND THE NEWS MEDIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
What could have been an affecting story based on the life of Camarena turned 
out to be a caricature of what is supposed to be life in Mexico under the 
influence of drug lords and corrupted officials. 
</P>
<P>
The series was full of the usual stereotypical and one-dimensional characters 
we've come to know in American television and movies. 
</P>
<P>
The Latin characters are all buffoons, crooks or both. Throughout the movie I 
kept waiting for someone to blurt the line: "Badges, we don't need any steenken 
badges!" 
</P>
<P>
Even Brokaw twice asked the question: "Do you think the President should have 
sent the Marines into Mexico?" Is he aware of the repercussions of such an 
action? Relations between our countries would be strained for generations! 
</P>
<P>
ROBERT LOLA, Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
