<TEXT>
<P>
DPC Ends Hostile Bid for Dataproducts: DPC Acquisition Corp., citing "disarray 
in the financial markets," ended its yearlong hostile effort to buy 
Dataproducts Corp. by scrapping a $190-million tender offer for the Woodland 
Hills maker of computer printers. The New York investor group, which already 
owns 7.5% of Dataproducts' stock, had offered $10 cash for each of the 
remaining shares. But since launching the offer in October, DPC's investment 
bankers had been unable to raise the cash. 
</P>
