<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: NORTH COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Diego City Councilwoman Abbe Wolfsheimer was selected Friday to chair the 
governing board of the San Dieguito River Valley Regional Open Space Park. She 
was nominated by County Supervisor Susan Golding, who was named vice chairwoman 
and will become chairwoman in a year. 
</P>
<P>
The two had served as co-chairwomen of the joint powers authority overseeing 
the planning and development of the 43-mile-long park, which is proposed to 
wind from Del Mar to the foothills of Julian. 
</P>
<P>
Named interim executive director of the park agency was Diane Barlow-Coombs, 
who has served as administrative aide to Supervisor George Bailey and other 
county supervisors before him. 
</P>
<P>
She replaces Mike Gotch, a former San Diego city councilman who was named 
agency director but resigned shortly afterward so he could run for the 78th 
Assembly seat vacated by Lucy Killea. 
</P>
