SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: ESCONDIDO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A migrant worker was shot to death in his makeshift shack Thursday night, 
apparently after an argument with a friend, who was arrested on suspicion of 
murder. 
</P>
<P>
Pablo Yanez was found dead of a gunshot wound in the chest in a grove south of 
the 3100 block of Summit Drive, after his alleged assailant, 36-year-old Jose 
Tavera, telephoned the San Diego County Sheriff's Department to report the 
incident, Sheriff's Sgt. Manny Castillo said. 
</P>
<P>
Tavera, also a laborer, was arrested without incident. 
</P>
