<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
LA QUINTA ROLLS TO 47TH STRAIGHT LEAGUE VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Center Amy Jalewalia scored 32 points, had nine rebounds and six assists to 
lead La Quinta High School to a 82-39 victory over host Garden Grove Friday 
night in a Garden Grove League girls' basketball game. 
</P>
<P>
La Quinta, which improved to 16-2 overall and 7-0 in league play, recorded its 
47th consecutive league victory. 
</P>
<P>
Tonya Krill added 19 points and Heather Brannan had 12 for La Quinta. 
</P>
<P>
Melanie Dear scored 18 for Garden Grove (8-7, 4-3). 
</P>
<P>
In other Garden Grove League games: 
</P>
<P>
Los Amigos 55, Santiago 41 -- Carrie Elsaesser had 16 points to lead host Los 
Amigos (7-9, 2-5). May Ly had 12 points and Uyen Nguyen had 11 for Los Amigos. 
Becky Elcock had 17 points for Santiago. 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy 69, Pacifica 31 -- Valerie Ruiz scored a game-high 33 points, including 
23 in the first half, to lead visiting Kennedy (9-8, 5-2). Ruiz, a junior point 
guard, also had a season-high 12 steals. Michelle Harris added 12 points for 
Kennedy. 
</P>
