<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP SOCCER ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
ORANGE MAKES THINGS PERFECTLY CLEAR BY BEATING LAGUNA HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS KAISER In other Pacific Coast League matches: Woodbridge 1, Trabuco 
Hills 0 -- Mike Mendoza scored in the second half for host Woodbridge. Eric 
Mooberry had eight saves for Woodbridge. In the Century League: Villa Park 3, 
El Modena 2 -- 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Orange High School's 2-0 victory over host Laguna Hills in a boys' soccer match 
Friday helped clear up what would have been a cloudy picture. 
</P>
<P>
The victory improved Orange's record to 11-0-2 overall and 9-0 in the Pacific 
Coast League. Laguna Hills, trying to gain a tie for the league lead, fell to 
14-3, 7-2. 
</P>
<P>
"We wanted to make that third-round game (against Orange Feb. 7) mean 
something," Laguna Hills Coach Scott Johnson said. 
</P>
<P>
Instead, the Panthers strengthened their hold on first place. 
</P>
<P>
Tres Martin had 12 saves in recording his seventh shutout of the season for 
Orange, ranked second in the Southern Section 2-A Division. 
</P>
<P>
"We wanted to clinch league, go undefeated and beat them here," said Orange 
halfback Ricky Heimer, who scored his ninth goal of the season. With 16 minutes 
remaining, Heimer scored on a rebound of Tim Huhn's shot. 
</P>
<P>
Huhn accounted for the first goal when he broke free down the left sideline and 
beat Laguna Hills goalkeeper Kirk Brown 13 minutes into the second half. 
</P>
<P>
The assist went to Heimer, who predicted afterward: "We're going to win CIF," 
he said. "Righetti (ranked No. 1), forget it. They may as well go home." 
</P>
<P>
For 50 minutes it looked as if both teams would go home empty-handed. 
</P>
<P>
"You've got to be patient in a game like this," Heimer said. "If you wait for 
it, it will come." 
</P>
<P>
Said Martin: "The key was they (Orange's forwards) just kept on pushing it up 
field and we got those breakaways." 
</P>
<P>
Martin and Justin Zayas, a 5-foot-6 fullback, anchored a defense that shut down 
Laguna Hills' leading scorer, Brian Slayback. 
</P>
<P>
"They didn't take many shots that he (Martin) had to make great saves on," 
Orange Coach Ed Carrillo said. "And with Justin (Zayas) in back, we can attack 
and push harder." DENNIS KAISER In other Pacific Coast League matches: 
Woodbridge 1, Trabuco Hills 0 -- Mike Mendoza scored in the second half for 
host Woodbridge. Eric Mooberry had eight saves for Woodbridge. In the Century 
League: Villa Park 3, El Modena 2 -- Junior Keith Amen scored to break a 2-2 
tie in the second half for host Villa Park (6-4-3, 1-2-1). Amen had two goals 
and David Szekeres also scored for Villa Park. Steve Wiser and Ronnie Murrietta 
scored for El Modena (1-2-1 in league play). Foothill 0, Santa Ana Valley 0 -- 
Lance Anderson had six saves for host Foothill (15-2-3, 2-0-2) and Marcellino 
Barriga had 13 saves for Santa Ana Valley. Santa Ana 2, Canyon 1 -- Rafael 
Segovia and Robert Sanchez scored for host Santa Ana (11-2-5, 3-0-1). Steve 
Frize scored for Canyon (7-7-3, 0-2-2) to tie the match at 1-1 with about 10 
minutes remaining. Sanchez scored the winning goal one minute later. In the 
Empire League: El Dorado 5, Loara 1 -- Derrick Dean had two goals, Tom Guenther 
had one goal and one assist, and Kirk Jorgenson and Tim Sesson each scored for 
visiting El Dorado (10-6-6, 2-2-1). Anthony Bravo scored for Loara. Los 
Alamitos 2, Esperanza 1 -- Jared Abe and Todd Platt scored for host Los 
Alamitos in an upset of fourth-ranked Esperanza ( at halftime, but Platt scored 
four minutes into the second half. In the Garden Grove League: La Quinta 6, 
Garden Grove 0 -- Chris Doherty had three goals for visiting La Quinta. Craig 
Wickenberg, Dave Matlock and Chris Siok also scored for La Quinta (8-6-4, 
4-0-3). Pacifica 1, Kennedy 0 -- Phil Noetzel scored about 10 minutes into the 
second half for host Pacifica. Erick Cadacio had 15 saves and blocked a penalty 
kick with five minutes remaining for Pacifica. In the Orange League: Valencia 
2, Savanna 1 -- Danny Melia and Steve Johnson scored to lead visiting Valencia, 
which improved to 4-0 in league. Valencia led, 2-0, at halftime. Goalie Yaya 
Jahadi had nine saves and Matt Labhart helped control the game's tempo for 
Valencia. Brea-Olinda 2, Magnolia 0 -- Jason Ochs scored twice on two assists 
by Martin Wall to lead host Brea-Olinda (8-8-1, 2-1). Jeff Bettencourt had 
seven saves for Brea-Olinda in recording his sixth shutout of the season. In 
the Sea View League: Estancia 2, Tustin 1 -- Gary Burrows and Ceasar Ovando 
scored for host Estancia (6-7-1, 3-1). Dan Choi scored for Tustin. University 
2, Corona del Mar 1 -- Paul Simon had both goals off assists by Diego Serrano 
to lead visiting University (7-5-2, 1-2-1). Alfredo Sandoval scored for Corona 
del Mar, which fell to 2-2 in league play. Goalie Chris Connelly had eight 
saves for Corona del Mar, and Robert Haworth had five saves for University. 
Saddleback 3, Newport Harbor 3 -- Alex Opoulos scored for host Newport Harbor 
with about three minutes left for the tie. Brian Mallin and Brannon Coluccio 
also scored for Newport Harbor (15-3-2, 3-0-1). Braulio Mendez, Jose Perez and 
Elio Cisneros scored for Saddleback (1-2-1 in league play). In the Sunset 
League: Huntington Beach 1, Fountain Valley 1 -- Tom Jackson scored for 
Fountain Valley and Olman Zamora scored for Huntington Beach. In the Olympic 
League: Orange Lutheran 3, Whitney 0 -- Travis Haynes, Lee Back and Sean Tully 
scored for host Orange Lutheran (8-1-2, 6-1). Santa Margarita 4, Capistrano 
Valley Christian 0 -- Travis Luvero scored twice and Tim Markel and Oscar 
Mestre once each for host Santa Margarita (5-9, 3-3). Dan Peters had two saves 
for Santa Margarita. In a Garden Grove League girls' match: Kennedy 3, Pacifica 
1 -- Krista Darin, Lori Van Herk and Adriane Poan scored for host Kennedy 
(10-4, 3-1). In an Olympic League girls' match: Orange Lutheran 4, St. 
Margaret's 0 -- Freshman forward Amber Parkinson had three goals for visiting 
Orange Lutheran (10-2-2, 5-1-2). Brandi Yates added the other goal for the 
Lancers. Parkinson scored eight goals in three matches this week and has 21 
goals in 14 matches for the season. Amy DuPont had six saves as she recorded 
her eighth shutout of the season for Orange Lutheran. St. Margaret's is 3-5-2, 
1-5-1. 
</P>
