<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
TURNER PACES CAL STATE L.A. PAST CHAPMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bruce Turner scored 16 points and LaVar Ball added 14 to lead Cal State Los 
Angeles to a 64-54 victory over Chapman in a California Collegiate Athletic 
Assn. game Friday at Cal State Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
Cal State L.A. opened a 23-8 lead after 9 1/2 minutes and led, 37-27, at the 
half. 
</P>
<P>
Cal State L.A. is 7-8 overall and 1-2 in conference play. 
</P>
<P>
Frantz Reyes scored 19, Andre Hill had 14 and Roger Middleton 10 for Chapman 
(9-7, 1-2). Middleton, who is shooting 70% this season, made four of 10 shots 
and had nine rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
In California Collegiate Athletic Assn. women's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
Chapman 82, Cal State Los Angeles 70 -- Julie King had 18 points, Jackie 
Saunders had 17 and Bethel Trice had 16 for visiting Chapman (13-5, 1-2). 
Saunders and Trice each had 13 rebounds for Chapman. 
</P>
<P>
In men's nonconference swimming: 
</P>
<P>
Arizona 83.5, UC Irvine 34.5 -- Senior Brian Judd won the 200-yard freestyle 
with a time of 1 minute 44.1 seconds and the 500 freestyle in 4:40.3 for UC 
Irvine (5-2) at Arizona (1-2). Irvine sophomore Jeff Klatt won the 100 
butterfly in 51.47 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
In women's nonconference swimming: 
</P>
<P>
Arizona 82, UC Irvine 40 -- Sophomore Danielle Pajer won the 100 breaststroke 
(1:08.7) and the 200 breaststroke (2:29.82) for UC Irvine (3-4) at Arizona 
(2-1). Pajer came in second in the 50 freestyle (25.67) to Jennifer Carper 
(25.62). 
</P>
