<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: UCSD WINS, PLAYS REGION LEADER TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tom Shawcroft scored 14 points, and Tim Rapp added 12 to lead UC San Diego to 
an 81-60 nonconference victory over visiting UC Santa Cruz Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
The Tritons (12-4 and ranked No. 2 in the NCAA Division III West Region) will 
play host to Menlo College, the region's top-ranked team, tonight at 7:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Cruz's Banana Slugs fell to 3-15. 
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
Cal State San Bernardino won its 12th in row, defeating visiting UC San Diego, 
86-79, in a Division III nonconference game. 
</P>
<P>
Cari Young (22 points) and Lisa Beaver (17) led UCSD (9-6). Teri Walsh led San 
Bernardino (13-3) with 20. San Bernardino led by just 70-68 with 5:54 remaining 
but went on a 12-3 run over the next 4:40. 
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S GOLF 
</P>
<P>
San Diego State finished fifth in the Yamaha Holiday Golf Tournament at Carlton 
Oaks Country Club in Santee. SDSU's Joann Walker finished tied for eighth with 
a score of 156 after a 79 Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Arizona State won the tournament, led by Brandie Burton and Amy Fruwirth, who 
tied for first at 148. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA's Christy Erb, who played in high school at USDHS, finished in a three-way 
tie for fifth with a score of 155. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Northridge rallied from a 2-0 deficit to defeat host San Diego State, 
6-15, 15-17, 15-7, 15-13, 15-11, in the Aztecs' season opener. 
</P>
<P>
Neil Coffman had 30 kills for Northridge (1-1). Douglas Potter had 19 kills, 
and Mike Mattarocci. 
</P>
