<HEADLINE>
<P>
$500,000 IN ANTIQUES, INCLUDING SHERMAN'S SWORD, RECOVERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAVANNAH, Ga. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Investigators say they have recovered more than $500,000 in stolen antiques -- 
including two centuries-old violins and a sword reportedly used by Civil War 
Gen. William T. Sherman. 
</P>
<P>
The merchandise, which included books, coin collections, toy cars and guns, was 
found Thursday in a storage locker. 
</P>
<P>
Police have arrested 29 people since a grand jury in Columbus, Ohio, returned 
secret indictments on Jan. 2 in connection with an Ohio-based burglary ring, 
but no arrests involving the Savannah cache have been made. 
</P>
<P>
The Sherman-related items, which included a portrait of the Union general, were 
stolen from the museum at Sherman's birthplace in Lancaster, Ohio, 
investigators said. 
</P>
