<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIRST PICK NINE OF SEASON WORTH $259,201 TO WINNER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A single Pick Nine ticket purchased at a Santa Anita Inter-Track Wagering site 
on Friday had the winners of all nine races and was worth $259,201 to the fan 
holding it. The ticket had not been cashed at the close of the day. 
</P>
<P>
This is the first time in the first 20 days of the winter-spring meeting that 
the Pick Nine has been won. The pool included a carryover of $240,755 from 
Thursday's program. 
</P>
<P>
The biggest longshot on the winning ticket came in the first race when No. 4, 
Rainbeau For Becky, paid $17 to win. In order, the other winning numbers, 
horses and win mutuels were: (3) Lager ($10.60), (5) Senegalaise ($8.20), (5) 
Vital Decision ($7.80), (5) Bit O'Dip ($7.80), (5) Perforce ($5.40), (4) For My 
Friends ($3.80), (4) Complicate ($9.20), (7) Greek Turf ($8.20). 
</P>
