<P>
RECORD COCAINE BUST ALSO NETS GUNS, CASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT LAIT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the city's largest cocaine bust ever, Orange police announced Friday the 
seizure of more than 70 kilograms of the drug, four handguns and $500,000 in 
cash as a result of a monthlong narcotics investigation. 
</P>
<P>
Police arrested two suspects in connection with the investigation that 
originated in Orange and led them to houses in Glendale and Century City, and a 
warehouse in downtown Los Angeles, Orange Police Sgt. Art Romo said. 
</P>
<P>
"It's the biggest coke seizure we've ever had," he said. 
</P>
<P>
Romo declined to release the names of the suspects, whom he identified as 
Colombian men. 
</P>
<P>
He said the information might hamper the ongoing investigation. 
</P>
<P>
Burbank and Glendale police helped serve search warrants at the three locations 
Thursday night, Romo said. MATT LAIT 
</P>
</TEXT>
